Slave Ship

History Documentary hosted by Alfre Woodard, published by Discovery Channel in 1997 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

Slave ship. In 1839 a strong man was kidnapped in his native Africa, marched for months in deadly heat to the coast, hauled across the ocean, and sold into slavery as part of the largest forced migration in human history. But what happened next inspired the world. While being transported on the Spanish merchant schooner Amistad, the African, Cinque, led a mutiny which saved him and the other imprisoned Africans from slavery, making Cinque a world renowned hero.
This amazing event spanned two continents and was an early test of the American legal process. Dramatic re-creations and enlightening interviews reveal a courageous story that inspired the world.

Producer/Writer : Richard Rivera
Director : Noah Morowitz
Produced by Matter/Rivera Productions For Discovery Channel

